The removal and potential recyclability of a catalyst from the reaction mechanism at the completion of the process is the key advantage of photocatalysis systems. As a result, the utilization of a catalyst in research was studied further shown in Fig. 11
                        . The catalyst's durability was examined by filtering, and rinsing it with water, then drying it at 80 °C before using it in the next catalysis cycle. However, after 4 runs, the efficiency of Ag-AC nanocomposite for photodegradation of textile effluent remains stable at around 90 %, confirming that the recovered catalysts are reliable and efficient for the degradation of textile effluent samples (see Figs. 12 and 13

                        ).
